02:25:48,361 --> 02:25:53,298
Benjamin Button,
this is my husband, Robert.

1676
02:25:53,399 --> 02:25:55,799
- How do you do?
- A pleasure.

1677
02:26:03,943 --> 02:26:06,935
Well, it was very nice to meet you.

1678
02:26:07,046 --> 02:26:08,843
- We'll be in the car, darling.
- All right.

1679
02:26:08,948 --> 02:26:10,074
Bye.

1680
02:26:10,817 --> 02:26:12,580
I'm just locking up.

1681
02:26:17,356 --> 02:26:18,414
Wow.

1682
02:26:20,960 --> 02:26:23,827
She's beautiful. Like her mother.

1683
02:26:25,431 --> 02:26:27,899
- Does she dance?
- Not very well.

1684
02:26:28,000 --> 02:26:29,900
I guess that'd be
from my side of things.

1685
02:26:30,002 --> 02:26:31,993
She's a dear, sweet girl.

1686
02:26:33,206 --> 02:26:37,540
She seems a little lost.
But then, who isn't at 12?

1687
02:26:37,744 --> 02:26:41,976
A lot of her reminds me of you.

1688
02:26:42,882 --> 02:26:46,818
My husband, he's a widower, or was...
Was a widower.

1689
02:26:47,220 --> 02:26:51,122
He's an incredibly kind, just bright,
adventurous man.

1690
02:26:54,293 --> 02:26:56,989
- He's been a terrific father.
- Good.

1691
02:27:01,701 --> 02:27:05,603
- You are so much younger.
- Only on the outside.

1692
02:27:07,707 --> 02:27:09,231
You were right.

1693
02:27:11,010 --> 02:27:14,377
I couldn't have been raising both of you.

1694
02:27:14,480 --> 02:27:16,243
I'm not that strong.

1695
02:27:20,453 --> 02:27:22,478
So, where are you staying?

1696
02:27:25,158 --> 02:27:26,147
What are you gonna do?

1697
02:27:26,259 --> 02:27:30,059
I'm staying at the Pontchartrain Hotel
on the Avenue.

1698
02:27:30,163 --> 02:27:33,690
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

1699
02:27:33,800 --> 02:27:34,960
But...

1700
02:27:41,474 --> 02:27:43,101
They're waiting.

1701
02:28:25,251 --> 02:28:28,516
I remember that. That was him?

1702
02:28:31,190 --> 02:28:32,350
The hurricane has changed directions.

1703
02:28:32,458 --> 02:28:34,289
It's going to make landfall
sometime soon.

1704
02:28:34,393 --> 02:28:36,122
- Am I supposed to do something?
- Arrangements are being made

1705
02:28:36,229 --> 02:28:37,457
to move people, but it's up to you.

1706
02:28:37,563 --> 02:28:39,428
No. No, we're... We're staying.

1707
02:28:39,532 --> 02:28:42,160
I'll let you know if anything changes.

1708
02:28:44,203 --> 02:28:48,537
"That night, while I was sitting
and wondering why I came back at all,

1709
02:28:48,641 --> 02:28:50,973
"there was a knock at the door. "

1710
02:28:54,614 --> 02:28:55,842
Come in.

1711
02:29:10,162 --> 02:29:11,823
Are you all right?

1712
02:29:14,934 --> 02:29:19,030
I'm sorry,
I don't know what I'm doing here.

1713
02:29:28,080 --> 02:29:29,570
Nothing lasts.

1714
02:29:33,052 --> 02:29:35,384
I have never stopped loving you.

1715
02:29:41,394 --> 02:29:44,090
Oh, but, Benjamin,
I'm an old woman now.

1716
02:29:54,740 --> 02:29:56,935
Some things you never forget.

1717
02:30:17,229 --> 02:30:18,287
<i>...so few people even know</i>

1718
02:30:18,397 --> 02:30:20,092
<i>that you were ever in jail
in the first place.</i>

1719
02:30:20,199 --> 02:30:22,394
<i>I'll tell you, I am sick about it, too,</i>

1720
02:30:22,501 --> 02:30:25,061
<i>because, please,
if they're not gonna give you an award</i>

1721
02:30:25,171 --> 02:30:27,230
<i>like "Man of the Year,"
at least what they could do</i>

1722
02:30:27,340 --> 02:30:30,002
<i>is stop having you listed
as an ex-convict</i>

1723
02:30:30,109 --> 02:30:32,600
<i>which I think is, again, so unfair.</i>

1724
02:30:45,391 --> 02:30:47,188
Good night, Benjamin.

1725
02:30:48,728 --> 02:30:50,389
Good night, Daisy.

1726
02:30:53,599 --> 02:30:57,831
<i>And as I knew I would,
I watched her go.</i>

1727
02:31:00,573 --> 02:31:02,871
That's the last thing he wrote.

1728
02:31:04,043 --> 02:31:08,605
Sometime after your father passed,

1729
02:31:08,714 --> 02:31:11,547
there was a call.

1730
02:31:14,620 --> 02:31:15,780
Hello.

1731
02:31:16,889 --> 02:31:18,379
Yes, speaking.

1732
02:31:21,727 --> 02:31:24,218
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

1733
02:31:34,073 --> 02:31:35,938
It's the corner house.

1734
02:31:58,130 --> 02:31:59,495
Come on in.

1735
02:32:05,104 --> 02:32:07,129
- I'm Daisy Fuller.
- I'm David Hernandez,

1736
02:32:07,239 --> 02:32:10,936
with the Orleans Parish Department
of Child Welfare Services.

1737
02:32:11,043 --> 02:32:13,671
He was living in a condemned building.

1738
02:32:15,481 --> 02:32:17,779
The police found this with him.

1739
02:32:17,883 --> 02:32:20,818
This address.
It's got your name in it a lot.

1740
02:32:22,021 --> 02:32:24,649
He's in very poor health.
He was taken to the hospital.

1741
02:32:24,757 --> 02:32:28,784
He doesn't seem to know who
or where he is. He's very confused.

1742
02:32:28,894 --> 02:32:32,455
I was telling Mr. Hernandez
that Benjamin is one of us.

1743
02:32:32,565 --> 02:32:36,399
If he needs a place to stay,
it's all right, he can stay here.

1744
02:33:05,865 --> 02:33:07,127
Benjamin?

1745
02:33:11,003 --> 02:33:12,800
You play beautifully.

1746
02:33:16,308 --> 02:33:18,139
He doesn't seem to like to be touched.

1747
02:33:18,244 --> 02:33:19,905
He goes in and out
of states of recognition.

1748
02:33:20,012 --> 02:33:21,639
The doctors say,
if they didn't know any better,

1749
02:33:21,747 --> 02:33:24,181
he has the beginnings of dementia.

1750
02:33:25,985 --> 02:33:27,714
Do you remember me?

1751
02:33:30,890 --> 02:33:32,221
I'm Daisy.

1752
02:33:34,827 --> 02:33:36,294
I'm Benjamin.

1753
02:33:42,001 --> 02:33:44,663
It's nice to meet you, Benjamin.

1754
02:33:46,372 --> 02:33:51,742
Would you mind if I sit with you?
I would love to hear you play.

1755
02:33:55,614 --> 02:33:57,104
Do I know you?

1756
02:34:02,087 --> 02:34:03,714
<i>- I want some breakfast.
- And every day,</i>

1757
02:34:03,822 --> 02:34:07,781
<i>I would stop by to make sure
that he was comfortable.</i>

1758
02:34:07,893 --> 02:34:10,521
- No, I didn't.
- You just finished eating.

1759
02:34:10,629 --> 02:34:12,961
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing!

1760
02:34:13,065 --> 02:34:15,795
You're all fucking liars!

1761
02:34:15,901 --> 02:34:18,826
He doesn't believe
he just had his breakfast.

1762
02:34:20,139 --> 02:34:23,768
Now, why don't we see

1763
02:34:23,876 --> 02:34:27,243
if we can't find something else
for you to do?

1764
02:34:27,413 --> 02:34:30,576
I have a feeling
there's a lot of things I can't remember.

1765
02:34:30,683 --> 02:34:32,583
Well, like what, sugar?

1766
02:34:33,852 --> 02:34:37,845
It's like there's this whole life I had,

1767
02:34:39,325 --> 02:34:41,725
and I can't remember what it was.

1768
02:34:44,530 --> 02:34:45,861
It's okay.

1769
02:34:47,967 --> 02:34:49,434
It's okay to forget things.

1770
02:34:49,668 --> 02:34:55,231
<i>Many times, he would simply forget
who or where he was.</i>

1771
02:34:55,574 --> 02:34:57,235
There he is, he's up there on the roof.

1772
02:34:57,343 --> 02:34:59,038
<i>It wasn't easy.</i>

1773
02:34:59,144 --> 02:35:01,374
- Benjamin!
- I can see everything!

1774
02:35:01,480 --> 02:35:03,243
- I can see the big river!
- That's right,

1775
02:35:03,349 --> 02:35:05,078
you can see everything, sweetheart.

1776
02:35:05,184 --> 02:35:07,175
I can see the graveyard
where Mama's buried,

1777
02:35:07,286 --> 02:35:10,653
- and all those other people.
- I want you to come down!

1778
02:35:10,756 --> 02:35:14,487
- What if I could fly?
- I knew a man who could fly.

1779
02:35:15,494 --> 02:35:18,463
You come down
and I'll tell you all about him.

1780
02:35:22,034 --> 02:35:23,626
Somebody go up there.

1781
02:35:30,242 --> 02:35:33,211
<i>He was five when I moved in.</i>

1782
02:35:33,312 --> 02:35:37,772
<i>Nearly the same age I was
when I had met him.</i>

1783
02:35:43,789 --> 02:35:47,725
"This is the picture
of Old Man Kangaroo

1784
02:35:47,826 --> 02:35:50,260
"at 5:00 in the afternoon

1785
02:35:50,362 --> 02:35:53,820
"when he had got
his beautiful hind legs. "

1786
02:35:55,067 --> 02:35:56,364
<i>The days passed.</i>

1787
02:35:56,468 --> 02:36:00,700
<i>And I watched as he forgot how to walk</i>

1788
02:36:05,944 --> 02:36:08,378
<i>- and how to talk.
- What's my name?</i>

1789
02:36:08,847 --> 02:36:10,178
I'm Daisy.

1790
02:36:11,350 --> 02:36:13,113
Can you say "Daisy"?

1791
02:36:14,687 --> 02:36:19,954
<i>In 2002, they put up a new clock
in that train station.</i>

1792
02:36:26,799 --> 02:36:30,565
<i>And in the spring of 2003,</i>

1793
02:36:34,940 --> 02:36:36,601
<i>he looked at me</i>

1794
02:36:39,111 --> 02:36:44,174
<i>and I knew that he knew who I was.</i>

1795
02:36:47,720 --> 02:36:53,522
<i>And then he closed his eyes
as if to go to sleep.</i>

1796
02:37:26,091 --> 02:37:30,255
- I wish I'd known him.
- Now you do.

1797
02:37:34,767 --> 02:37:38,533
Mom, I think I should go see
what's going on.

1798
02:37:45,577 --> 02:37:47,602
Good night, Benjamin.

1799
02:38:10,002 --> 02:38:12,368
<i>We're expecting flash flooding
after the levee break.</i>

1800
02:38:12,471 --> 02:38:14,701
<i>It occurred in the Ninth Ward.</i>

1801
02:38:17,743 --> 02:38:20,576
<i>Some people are born to sit by a river.</i>

1802
02:38:22,114 --> 02:38:24,048
<i>Some get struck by lightning.</i>

1803
02:38:25,951 --> 02:38:28,044
<i>Some have an ear for music.</i>

1804
02:38:29,655 --> 02:38:31,282
<i>Some are artists.</i>

1805
02:38:32,624 --> 02:38:33,955
<i>Some swim.</i>

1806
02:38:35,394 --> 02:38:37,021
<i>Some know buttons.</i>

1807
02:38:38,831 --> 02:38:40,196
<i>Some know Shakespeare.</i>

1808
02:38:41,366 --> 02:38:43,129
<i>Some are mothers.</i>

1809
02:38:45,103 --> 02:38:48,129
<i>And some people dance.</i>

